@startuml
title Identity and Account Flows

actor User
participant Frontend
participant AuthController
participant OAuth2Controller as "OAuth2AuthController"
participant AuthService
participant OAuth2Service as "OAuth2AuthService"
participant PasswordResetService
database UserRepo
database OAuth2AccountRepo
database RefreshTokenRepo
database OtpRepo as "PasswordResetOtpRepository"
participant JwtProvider
participant Google as "Google OAuth2"
participant MailService as "AuthMailService"

== Register / Login ==
User -> Frontend : Register or login
Frontend -> AuthController : POST /api/v1/auth/register|login
AuthController -> AuthService : register(req) / login(req)
AuthService -> UserRepo : save/find user
UserRepo --> AuthService : user
AuthService -> JwtProvider : generateAccessToken(user)
AuthService -> JwtProvider : generateRefreshToken()
AuthService -> RefreshTokenRepo : save refresh token hash
AuthService --> AuthController : AuthResponse
AuthController --> Frontend : access + refresh token

== Refresh Token ==
Frontend -> AuthController : POST /api/v1/auth/refresh
AuthController -> AuthService : refresh(req)
AuthService -> RefreshTokenRepo : validate token hash
AuthService -> RefreshTokenRepo : revoke old token
AuthService -> JwtProvider : generate new token pair
AuthService -> RefreshTokenRepo : save new refresh token hash
AuthService --> AuthController : AuthResponse
AuthController --> Frontend : rotated tokens

== Google OAuth2 Login ==
User -> Frontend : Click Google sign-in
Frontend -> Google : request identity token
Google --> Frontend : Google ID token
Frontend -> OAuth2Controller : POST /api/v1/auth/oauth2/google
OAuth2Controller -> OAuth2Service : authenticateGoogle(token)
OAuth2Service -> Google : verify token
Google --> OAuth2Service : profile + claims
OAuth2Service -> OAuth2AccountRepo : find provider link
alt Existing OAuth2 account
  OAuth2AccountRepo --> OAuth2Service : existing link
  OAuth2Service -> UserRepo : load user
else First OAuth2 login
  OAuth2AccountRepo --> OAuth2Service : not found
  OAuth2Service -> UserRepo : find by email or create user
  OAuth2Service -> OAuth2AccountRepo : save oauth2 account link
end
OAuth2Service -> AuthService : buildTokensForUser(user)
AuthService -> JwtProvider : generate access token
AuthService -> JwtProvider : generate refresh token
AuthService -> RefreshTokenRepo : save refresh token hash
AuthService --> OAuth2Service : AuthResponse
OAuth2Service --> OAuth2Controller : AuthResponse
OAuth2Controller --> Frontend : access + refresh token

== Password Reset ==
User -> Frontend : Forgot password
Frontend -> AuthController : POST /api/v1/auth/forgot-password
AuthController -> PasswordResetService : requestOtp(email)
PasswordResetService -> UserRepo : lookup eligible account
alt Eligible account exists
  UserRepo --> PasswordResetService : user found
  PasswordResetService -> OtpRepo : save OTP hash + expiry
  PasswordResetService -> MailService : send OTP email
  MailService --> PasswordResetService : accepted
else No eligible account
  UserRepo --> PasswordResetService : none
end
PasswordResetService --> AuthController : generic success
AuthController --> Frontend : "If eligible, OTP sent"

User -> Frontend : Submit OTP + new password
Frontend -> AuthController : POST /api/v1/auth/reset-password
AuthController -> PasswordResetService : resetPassword(req)
PasswordResetService -> OtpRepo : load valid OTP
PasswordResetService -> PasswordResetService : verify hash + expiry
PasswordResetService -> UserRepo : update password hash
PasswordResetService -> OtpRepo : mark consumed
PasswordResetService --> AuthController : success
AuthController --> Frontend : password reset complete
@enduml
